Geez Cookie, I wanted to post your picture on the net.. local Medicine Man warned me that I might get sued for spreading a virus.<br><br>
Tried it anyway and my hard drive melted..speakers started squealing..and my monitor screen spider webbed, shattered and fell onto my Spam sandwich.<br><br>
I spent five years as a low life potatoe peeler before God realized his mistake and gave me some shiny bars.  Spent a lot of time with the troops.  It did me a lot of good and I want to believe that it did some of my men a bit of good.  Didn't give orders..just suggested stuff and it was done.  It was a special relationship that I enjoyed with crew members (probably where I got my sick sense of humor..from Enlisted Scum!)<br><br>
Most intense relationship with enlisted was with the Special Forces.  No rank..no bull.. just keep it simple stupid.  I often felt inferior to these amazing souls.  Found out later that they respected and admired me.  Cried openly over a few who died.<br><br>
Never did &quot;hit a hut&quot; or &quot;lock heels&quot; over matters of respect.  Didn't tolerate disrespect at all but only encountered the problem once in thirteen years...he was an E-6 who didn't know me or was he assigned to my unit.  I handed him over to a Sergeant Major who showed him how the cow ate the cabbage.<br><br>
Now..if you will pass the hot coffee.. shit for brains..you may stand &quot;at ease!&quot;<br><br>
Your Idol, Forever- MTF (Mostly Tough &amp; Famous) or (Mom's True Favorite) or (Marines Tribute Frequently)<br><br>
P.S.  Loved my men..and still do.  God Bless them wherever they are on this Veterans Day.
